\btitle{ The future of dialects: Selected papers from Methods in Dialectology XV }
\bauthor{Marie-Hélène Côté, Remco Knooihuizen, John Nerbonne}
\bisbn{4e235126231}
\bdoi{53244143} 
\bprice{50 EUR} 
\btagline{Traditional dialects have been encroached upon by the increasing mobility of their speakers and by the onslaught of national languages in education and mass media. }
\bblurb{Traditional dialects have been encroached upon by the increasing mobility of their speakers and by the onslaught of national languages in education and mass media.
Typically, older dialects are “leveling” to become more like national languages. This is regrettable when the last articulate traces of a culture are lost, but it also promotes a complex dynamics of interaction as speakers shift from dialect to standard and to intermediate compromises between the two in their forms of speech. }